post_text:
Merchants Bank in Caledonia is going to move forward with their annual windshield washing event. Each year Merchants washes windshields in their drive up and for each windshield they wash, they will donate $5 to a respective charitable organization. This year they have decided to donate the funds to the Caledonia Area Elementary/Middle/High School. The windshield washing event will be held on September 18th from 2 pm to 6 pm at the Merchants Bank - Caledonia drive thru.

No customer relationship is necessary to come through the drive up. They are just having a fun event to raise some money for the school. Free will donations are also accepted and would be passed along to the school also.

Thanks everyone for taking part in our Summer Food Service Program! Huge shout out to the bus drivers that helped deliver food to the communities in our district. We are looking forward to seeing everyone back in school starting August 24th. Breakfast and lunch may look different from other school year beginnings, with some fun changes that may become permanent. Watch the school website for menu postings soon.
Thank you to the kitchen crew, Bonnie, Vicky, Carrie, Debby, Lisa. Victoria, Janice, Eileen and honorary lunch staff--- Sue, Ann, Heidi, Kathy, and the custodians that helped haul and put the tent up and down. It's an honor to serve our families.

post_text:
Plans for returning:

We have many different ideas for how the kids will come back, but have not yet arrived at a precise plan.

Until we get the guidance from MDE, we don't want to provide much detail to any of the plans (which I know is frustrating for our families) in an effort to avoid confusion and speculation. I found out moments ago the guidance will come on July 30th.

I will say that we do have a plan to provide an online option for the group of students that may not be able to attend in person for a variety of reasons in either a hybrid or in person model.

Thank you for your continued patience as we figure this out.

post_text:
• Did your child participate in free or reduced-price school meals? Because schools are closed, a
new program can help provide a food benefit, take a moment to apply for P-EBT.
Apply today: www.mn.p-ebt.org
• As the COVID-19 pandemic continues to have wide-ranging health and economic impacts, please
know that there are opportunities to help you buy food.
Consider applying for P-EBT benefits: www.mn.p-ebt.org
• The Coronavirus continues to impact our communities in many ways. If you need assistance with
food, there are opportunities to get the nutritious food your family needs to stay healthy.
If you have children and were receiving SNAP or MFIP as of March 18, 2020, you will receive an
automatic benefit on your EBT card. If you weren’t receiving SNAP or MFIP but your child was
receiving free or reduced lunch, you can apply for P-EBT to help buy food for your family:
www.mn.p-ebt.org

APPLICATION DEADLINE EXTENDED FOR P-EBT
Families receiving free or reduced-price school meals on March 18 or prior for 19-20 school year, but not SNAP or MFIP benefits. These families need to fill out a short application for a P-EBT card. Families can apply between June 8, 2020, and July 31, 2020. If approved, families will receive a P-EBT card in the mail, which will arrive with the funds preloaded.
https://mn.p-ebt.org/en/
Please contact Rita McCormick by email or 507-725-3316 extension 2215 if you have any questions

post_text:
FREE SUMMER MEAL DELIVERY TO CONTINUE IN AREA COMMUNITIES for YOUTH 18 YEARS & YOUNGER
The decision has been made to continue to deliver meals to Eitzen, Brownsville and Freeburg.
We will be there next week, on June 30 at 11:00a.m. and July 2nd (watch for updates on time).
At this point our schedule for July and August is as follows:

No meal service July 6-10

July 13 - August 6th meals will be available on Tuesday and Thursday in Caledonia, Eitzen, Brownsville and Freeburg.

Also a reminder to families to check out the information on school website homepage about applying for the pandemic-electronic benefit card, this is for families that received lunch benefits during 19-20 school year, if you haven't received SNAP then you do need to apply $325.00/school age child to be used on food. Deadline to apply is June 30th.

post_text:
Minnesota is now offering funds for families of children ages 5 to 18 who qualify for free or reduced-price school meals. The new program, called Pandemic EBT (P-EBT), will provide up to $325 per child that families can use to purchase nutritious food for their household. Approximately 350,000 Minnesota children could benefit.
Learn more at: www.mn.p-ebt.org

post_text: The graduation program will be broadcasted tonight on 89.3 FM for family and friends who would like to listen to the graduation ceremony! Facebook Live will start a few minutes before the ceremony and the recording of the full graduation ceremony recording will be posted as soon as we are able, after the ceremony.
text: The graduation program will be broadcasted tonight on 89.3 FM for family and friends who would like to listen to the graduation ceremony! Facebook Live will start a few minutes before the ceremony and the recording of the full graduation ceremony recording will be posted as soon as we are able, after the ceremony.

post_text: Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, the 2020 graduation ceremony will be reserved for graduates and their immediate families only. Extended family and members of the public who wish to view the graduation ceremony, may attend via our Facebook live video. Graduation is scheduled for Friday, June 5th at 6:00pm. With a senior sendoff to follow the ceremony at approximately 6:45pm. The sendoff will leave from the MS/HS parking lot and go South down Gjere Ave. Cars will turn left at the stop sign and will head East down Main Street, ending at the Houston County Fairgrounds. The public is encouraged to attend the send off.
text: Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, the 2020 graduation ceremony will be reserved for graduates and their immediate families only. Extended family and members of the public who wish to view the graduation ceremony, may attend via our Facebook live video. Graduation is scheduled for Friday, June 5th at 6:00pm. With a senior sendoff to follow the ceremony at approximately 6:45pm. The sendoff will leave from the MS/HS parking lot and go South down Gjere Ave. Cars will turn left at the stop sign and will head East down Main Street, ending at the Houston County Fairgrounds. The public is encouraged to attend the send off.

post_text:
Senior Sendoff!

Following the graduation ceremony on Friday, June 5th, the Police and Fire Department will be leading the Class of 2020 through Caledonia. The route will leave the MS/HS parking lot and go South down Warrior/Gjere Ave. Cars will turn left at the stop sign and head East down Main Street, ending at the Houston County Fairgrounds. We estimate the send off to begin at approximately 6:45pm. Please join us in sending off our graduates to their next phases in life!

Summer Food for Caledonia Area Public Schools

June 1st–June 4th
We will continue with Tuesday & Thursday Meal Pick-up/Deliveries

We will have meals for three breakfasts in a white bag and three lunches in a brown bag on each pick up day at all the same delivery times.

June 8th–12th
Our kitchens will be closed and no busses will run with deliveries.

June 16th –June 30th
We will have meals for two days on Tuesdays and meals for three days on Thursdays.

We are waiting for confirmation on what our Summer Food Service Program will look like for July and August. We will pass that along as soon as we have clear direction from Minnesota Department of Education/School Food Nutrition.

Beginning on Wednesday, March 18th, child care will be available for Caledonia Area Public Schools children of healthcare and emergency workers*. The care will take place in the Caledonia Area Elementary School SAC classroom on weekdays from 6am-6pm. The fee for this care will be $2.75 per hour.

If you are eligible and interested in utilizing the child care that is being offered, please email gretchen_linzmeier@cps.k12.mn.us or leave a message at 507-725-3316, ext. 2013. In your message, please include your name, child(ren) name(s), place of employment, town you live in, and a phone number.

*Emergency workers (including providers of healthcare, emergency medical services, long-term and post-acute care; law enforcement personnel; personnel providing correctional services; public health employees; firefighters and other first responders; and court personnel)

post_text:
Veterans Day Programs – Monday, November 11th

Please join the Caledonia Area Public School students and staff as we honor all the men and women who served our country at our Veterans Day Programs on Monday, November 11th. The Elementary Veterans Day Program will begin at 8:30 a.m. in the Elementary Gymnasium. All Veterans are invited before the program for a complimentary breakfast being served in the elementary cafeteria from 7:45 a.m. until 8:30 a.m. The Middle/High School Veterans Day Program will begin at 10:30 a.m. in the MSHS auditorium. All Veterans are invited to stay after the program for a complimentary lunch in the MSHS common’s area. Please help us spread the word about our upcoming Veterans Day Programs and invite your friends and family, especially our Veterans. Everyone is welcome!

post_text:
Balanced Calendar Feedback Survey
The District 299 Board of Education is inviting everyone in the Brownsville, Caledonia, Eitzen, and Freeburg areas to join in a community-wide discussion and study of the school calendar. After much research, the Board is considering changing the school calendar. The Board believes that a balanced calendar may offer significant benefits for the education of our students. Please click the link to review more information and participate in a survey that relates to the balanced calendar. Thank you! Superintendent Craig Ihrke https://drive.google.com/file/d/1DwF-BpEV0XluSXk5IkNE-UpbggHat5S1/view?usp=sharing
